Installation instructions for btorrent
======================================

Quick install
-------------

    make
    sudo make install

This installs:
  /usr/local/bin/btorrent
  /usr/local/share/man/man1/btorrent.1

To install under /usr instead:

    sudo make install PREFIX=/usr

Staged install (for packaging)
-------------------------------

    make install DESTDIR=/tmp/pkg PREFIX=/usr

This installs into /tmp/pkg/usr/... without touching the live system,
which is the standard pattern for Debian, RPM, and AUR packages.

Build dependencies
------------------

  - C11 compiler: GCC >= 9 or Clang >= 11
  - libcurl >= 7.x  (Debian/Ubuntu: libcurl4-openssl-dev)
  - pkg-config

On Debian / Ubuntu:

    sudo apt install build-essential libcurl4-openssl-dev pkg-config

On Fedora / RHEL:

    sudo dnf install gcc libcurl-devel pkgconf-pkg-config

On Arch Linux:

    sudo pacman -S base-devel curl pkgconf

Uninstall
---------

    sudo make uninstall

Or manually:

    rm -f /usr/local/bin/btorrent
    rm -f /usr/local/share/man/man1/btorrent.1

Source tarball
--------------

    make dist

Produces btorrent-<VERSION>.tar.gz in the current directory.

Platform notes
--------------

btorrent uses Linux's epoll(7) API and is Linux-only. It will not build
on macOS or BSD without replacing the scheduler with kqueue or libuv.
